  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Providing a `searchState` object trigger a new search after checking that the props are not equals. \r\nIf it's the regular instantsearch query, it's fine because it's what you wan't. \r\n\r\nNow if we put the facetQuery inside the `searchState`, then it will go through the same process, and trigger a new global search. Which is not what we want (we only want the SFFV search). Therefore we need a way to differentiate both search. \r\n\r\nI think it's doable but it will change the way that the search is triggered now. ",
    "created_at": "2016-12-22T15:05:03Z",
